        private String getAccessToken(io.vertx.core.http.HttpServerRequest contextRequest)
        Obtains the access token from the request. It is expected to be the Authorization with a bearer tag. The authentication code is expected to be a given pattern.

        Returns:

      • handle

        public void handle(io.vertx.ext.web.RoutingContext context)
        This handler goes through the authorization to prepopulate the X-JWT-Assertion header. There is no need to check if client is authorized because it was already done by ClientOriginHandler.
